For $g(x)$ to be identical to its inverse $g^{-1}(x)$, we must have
$$g(x)=g^{-1}(x).$$
In other words, we must have
$$\frac{x+a-4}{x+a-3}=\frac{x+a-4}{x+a-3}.$$
This equation is true if and only if
$$x+a-4=x+a-3.$$
Solving for $a$, we get
$$a=\boxed{1}.$$

